{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.15",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 15,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 15",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 15 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:1",
      "text": "Then answered Eliphaz the Temanite, and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:2",
      "text": "Should a wise man utter vain knowledge, and fill his belly with the east wind?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:3",
      "text": "Should he reason with unprofitable talk? or with speeches wherewith he can do no good?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:4",
      "text": "Yea, thou castest off fear, and restrainest prayer before God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:5",
      "text": "For thy mouth uttereth thine iniquity, and thou choosest the tongue of the crafty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:6",
      "text": "Thine own mouth condemneth thee, and not I: yea, thine own lips testify against thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:7",
      "text": "Art thou the first man that was born? or wast thou made before the hills?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:8",
      "text": "Hast thou heard the secret of God? and dost thou restrain wisdom to thyself?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:9",
      "text": "What knowest thou, that we know not? what understandest thou, which is not in us?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:10",
      "text": "With us are both the grayheaded and very aged men, much elder than thy father.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:11",
      "text": "Are the consolations of God small with thee? is there any secret thing with thee?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:12",
      "text": "Why doth thine heart carry thee away? and what do thy eyes wink at,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:13",
      "text": "That thou turnest thy spirit against God, and lettest such words go out of thy mouth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:14",
      "text": "What is man, that he should be clean? and he which is born of a woman, that he should be righteous?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:15",
      "text": "Behold, he putteth no trust in his saints; yea, the heavens are not clean in his sight.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:16",
      "text": "How much more abominable and filthy is man, which drinketh iniquity like water?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:17",
      "text": "I will shew thee, hear me; and that which I have seen I will declare;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:18",
      "text": "Which wise men have told from their fathers, and have not hid it:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:19",
      "text": "Unto whom alone the earth was given, and no stranger passed among them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:20",
      "text": "The wicked man travaileth with pain all his days, and the number of years is hidden to the oppressor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:21",
      "text": "A dreadful sound is in his ears: in prosperity the destroyer shall come upon him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:22",
      "text": "He believeth not that he shall return out of darkness, and he is waited for of the sword.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:23",
      "text": "He wandereth abroad for bread, saying, Where is it? he knoweth that the day of darkness is ready at his hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:24",
      "text": "Trouble and anguish shall make him afraid; they shall prevail against him, as a king ready to the battle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:25",
      "text": "For he stretcheth out his hand against God, and strengtheneth himself against the Almighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:26",
      "text": "He runneth upon him, even on his neck, upon the thick bosses of his bucklers:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:27",
      "text": "Because he covereth his face with his fatness, and maketh collops of fat on his flanks.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:28",
      "text": "And he dwelleth in desolate cities, and in houses which no man inhabiteth, which are ready to become heaps.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:29",
      "text": "He shall not be rich, neither shall his substance continue, neither shall he prolong the perfection thereof upon the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.30",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:30",
      "text": "He shall not depart out of darkness; the flame shall dry up his branches, and by the breath of his mouth shall he go away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.31",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:31",
      "text": "Let not him that is deceived trust in vanity: for vanity shall be his recompence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.32",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:32",
      "text": "It shall be accomplished before his time, and his branch shall not be green.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.33",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:33",
      "text": "He shall shake off his unripe grape as the vine, and shall cast off his flower as the olive.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.34",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:34",
      "text": "For the congregation of hypocrites shall be desolate, and fire shall consume the tabernacles of bribery.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.15.35",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:35",
      "text": "They conceive mischief, and bring forth vanity, and their belly prepareth deceit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
